Each describe sensors call takes ~20ms, the rest of the time between calls in the cloud controller processing the returned sensor data.

Ideally we would:

* only describe instance sensor data on the cluster that was actually running that instance
* process clusters concurrently
* not interleave describing sensors and processing results

if that does not meet scale requirements we could have some concurrency for describing sensor data on each cluster.

Ideally describing sensors would take less than a minute in total (though the default interval is 5 minutes)

comments.body: This work is necessary to benefit from the CloudWatch scalability work that has already been done.
Could we also check only instances that are monitoring-enabled? There is no reason to request all instances from CC.

We now use a thread per cluster to retrieve sensor data concurrently. Processing of results is performed in separate threads and caching / projections are used to avoid excessive database access.

General testing of cloudwatch (and perhaps reporting) is sufficient to verify this issue, there should be no user visible changes other than performance.
